      <memberdef kind="function" id="options_8c_1a9ffa34edcd7016b99debd58250bba719" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>Object</type>
        <definition>Object nvim_get_option_value</definition>
        <argsstring>(String name, Dict(option) *opts, Error *err) FUNC_API_SINCE(9) FUNC_API_RET_ALLOC</argsstring>
        <name>nvim_get_option_value</name>
        <param>
          <type>String</type>
          <declname>name</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="struct_dict" kindref="compound">Dict</ref>(option) *</type>
          <declname>opts</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>Error *</type>
          <declname>err</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Gets the value of an option. The behavior of this function matches that of |:set|: the local value of an option is returned if it exists; otherwise, the global value is returned. Local values always correspond to the current buffer or window, unless &quot;buf&quot; or &quot;win&quot; is set in {opts}.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>name</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Option name </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>opts</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Optional parameters<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>scope: One of &quot;global&quot; or &quot;local&quot;. Analogous to |:setglobal| and |:setlocal|, respectively.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>win: |window-ID|. Used for getting window local options.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>buf: Buffer number. Used for getting buffer local options. Implies {scope} is &quot;local&quot;.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>filetype: |filetype|. Used to get the default option for a specific filetype. Cannot be used with any other option. Note: this will trigger |ftplugin| and all |FileType| autocommands for the corresponding filetype. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="out">err</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Error details, if any </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>Option value </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="D:/source/repos/neovim/src/nvim/api/options.c" line="151" column="8" bodyfile="D:/source/repos/neovim/src/nvim/api/options.c" bodystart="151" bodyend="207"/>
      </memberdef>
      <memberdef kind="function" id="options_8c_1a1eebeadb77319fb6964dc764daa649f4" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void nvim_set_option_value</definition>
        <argsstring>(uint64_t channel_id, String name, Object value, Dict(option) *opts, Error *err) FUNC_API_SINCE(9)</argsstring>
        <name>nvim_set_option_value</name>
        <param>
          <type>uint64_t</type>
          <declname>channel_id</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>String</type>
          <declname>name</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>Object</type>
          <declname>value</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="struct_dict" kindref="compound">Dict</ref>(option) *</type>
          <declname>opts</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>Error *</type>
          <declname>err</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Sets the value of an option. The behavior of this function matches that of |:set|: for global-local options, both the global and local value are set unless otherwise specified with {scope}.</para>
<para>Note the options {win} and {buf} cannot be used together.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>name</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Option name </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>value</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>New option value </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>opts</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Optional parameters<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>scope: One of &quot;global&quot; or &quot;local&quot;. Analogous to |:setglobal| and |:setlocal|, respectively.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>win: |window-ID|. Used for setting window local option.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>buf: Buffer number. Used for setting buffer local option. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="out">err</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Error details, if any </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
